         <abstract>
            <p>The inversive congruential method is a uniform pseudorandom number generator which was introduced recently. For a prime modulus $p$ the discrepancy $D^{(k)}_p$ of $k$-tuples of successive pseudorandom numbers generated by this method determines the statistical independence properties of these pseudorandom numbers. It was shown earlier by the author that $$D^{(k)}_p = O(p^{-1/2} (\log p)^k)\quad\text{for}\quad 2 \leq k &lt; p.$$ Here it is proved that this bound is essentially best possible. In fact, for a positive proportion of the admissible parameters in the inversive congruential method the discrepancy $D^{(k)}_p$ is at least of the order of magnitude $p^{-1/2}$ for all $k \geq 2$.</p>
          </abstract>
